result.name: LE PAN

reviews.text:
Slight disappointment but not because of the food.

It was a very unusual experience, first at the reception, identified by my phone number while my full uncomplicated name appears in my booking email.
The decoration is bright and clean however lacks uniqueness.
The menu was clear and simple but I couldn’t choose anything else than my wife’s choice.
The testing menu is well balanced and tasty but wines are overpriced and the service is below average compare to other fine dining places in Hongkong, as foods was presented somehow correctly but sans plus. 
Overall my palate was satisfied but fine dining is not just about food.

A very good restaurant with a unique dining experience. In the middle of the tasting menu, you are invited to go into the kitchen to have one of the course. The chef will make it in front of you and show you how they cook the main course. Food and service are extremely good as well.
Good food for sure. The atmosphere isn't very European though. More Macau than Milan

An impressive French restaurant located somewhat out-of -place in an industrial area of Kowloon Bay. Grand decor and surprisingly spacious. We were able to book a private room and the staff were very attentive and responsive. You would expect to pay a higher price for places like this, but weighed against the quality of the food, the price was in fact very very reasonable ($500 for 4 courses). Would definitely go again and highly recommended, especially for any corporate lunch/dinners. Impressed!

Beautiful resturant. Good vibes. Food are surprisingly amazing. Staffs are professional.
Highly recommend for anniversary or birthday celebration!
